article.headline: Murray State 65, Delaware State 56
article.story: DOVER, Del. (AP) -- Cuthbert Victor had 21 points and 12 rebounds to lead Murray State to a 65-56 win over Delaware State on Sunday. Antione Whelchel added 10 points and seven rebounds for the Racers (10-1), who made 22-of-45 shots, or 48.9 percent. Adam Chiles had eight points and five assists. Delaware State (1-6) was led by Jahsha Bluntt, who had 11 points, and Terrance Hunter and Carlos Hawkins added 10 points each. The loss snapped an 11-game home winning streak for the Hornets, who shot 42.6 percent (23-of-54) from the field. Delaware State went 11-0 at home last season. The Hornets made just 2-of-14 3-point attempts, while Murray State made 4-of-10. Murray State, which led 26-24 at halftime, went on an 11-2 run to start the second half, taking a 37-26 lead with 14:13 left.
